 " package is loaded to use the demonstrations in this documentation."
}], "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->1428640008,ExpressionUUID->"b98baad2-1630-4417-b3d5-1d951dc498bc"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",
 CellID->853967906,ExpressionUUID->"a40855f2-4211-4e36-ad92-3307ab07a32d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Definition", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->67330687,ExpressionUUID->"516b5151-b4ff-44b7-9b10-9715e1c57102"],

Cell["\<\
A classical probability distribution is associated with a random variable \
choosing values from a set of outcomes. In quantum mechanics, a density \
operator is associated with an ensemble of quantum states. One can imagine a \
quantum information source that generates messages of \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]letters\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] each of which is \
chosen from the ensemble.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1747924204,ExpressionUUID->"cd4edf34-e672-4ae4-ba20-a3683450e97a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["von Neumann entropy",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of a quantum state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Rho]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "59325661-42ab-4132-a5af-dc60f1bdd784"],
 " is defined by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->943524637,ExpressionUUID->"9b14df1d-811b-4aae-a248-06d8aeaa16b6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"S", "(", "\[Rho]", ")"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"\[Minus]", 
     RowBox[{"Tr", " ", "[", 
      RowBox[{"\[Rho]", " ", "log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[Rho]"}], "]"}]}]}],
    TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "886aa93f-58aa-4805-b273-02c7d1d09eab"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->354454418,ExpressionUUID->"edab5309-934b-438f-9703-ccc2469e2165"],

Cell["\<\
where the logarithm is with respect to base 2. A basic approach to evaluate \
the above expression is to take the spectral decomposition\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1045765700,ExpressionUUID->"9cfd8eed-84c5-42ca-8deb-9d70ec06438e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "\[Lambda]"], 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Lambda]"},
      "Ket"], "\[Lambda]", 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Lambda]"},
      "Bra"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e9985e65-4c6c-456f-96af-3bbb74c5b241"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->562472759,ExpressionUUID->"605c90bc-a08d-430a-8932-0fef5e51e88d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Lambda]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eb852ff6-74d0-4d91-bdaf-0874eeb1a64c"],
 " is the eigenvector of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Rho]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "06972084-7196-4fcf-a516-014d714db2d0"],
 " with eigenvalue ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Lambda]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8478e0ba-005c-46cd-a64b-41eb7e9a1697"],
 ". Given that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Rho]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "32aafdb1-9a75-4063-a7e8-61a6fe269d6c"],
 " is a positive operator, all the eigenvalues are non-negative, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "\[GreaterEqual]", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"6da89e9c-c2ac-456f-9609-baac4b8a699a"],
 ". Then, the von Neumann entropy is given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->227605959,ExpressionUUID->"aac006d5-7ca9-4d5c-a80f-ccd9288ff88f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"S", "(", "\[Rho]", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     UnderscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"-", "\[CapitalSigma]"}], "\[Lambda]"], "\[Lambda]", "\[VeryThinSpace]",
      "log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[Lambda]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"50f962b8-ce54-4481-ae37-234051fef807"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1855553708,ExpressionUUID->"98668c19-f5d4-404c-adb9-ac91dfab2ea8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In comparison with the ",
 ButtonBox["Shannon entropy",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/ShannonEntropy"],
 ", the eigenvalues play the role of probabilities. For zero eigenvalues (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "208ba1d1-4589-4eed-98b2-11ac4810c9f1"],
 "), we put ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"0", " ", "log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "0"}], "=", "0"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"4ef40624-2eb9-46d7-97f0-faab63e04b01"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1973174166,ExpressionUUID->"f9a6c1b9-3e2d-410c-9834-4d4057e911bb"],

Cell["For example, consider the density operator", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1401473804,ExpressionUUID->"25e06d73-2051-4da4-9b75-d7a79d636520"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["1", "2"], "I"}], "+", 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["1", "4"], "Y"}]}], "\[DotEqual]", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", "4"], 
      RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
         {"2", 
          RowBox[{"-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}]},
         {"\[ImaginaryI]", "2"}
        }], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e7b3c30a-92fd-4b43-b918-64078e43cb95"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->470983637,ExpressionUUID->"52395132-dc4a-4dbd-91d8-d56ae56292ea"],

Cell["\<\
It has two eigenvalues 1/4 and 3/4, and the von Neumann entropy is given by\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->116888411,ExpressionUUID->"ba925622-86b5-4109-90d3-9a8d4b36fe88"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"S", "(", "\[Rho]", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", "2"], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["3", "4"], "log", 
      FractionBox["3", "4"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e2bce6f2-bdd5-4ec4-96b2-19bc9cd55e7a"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->976075268,ExpressionUUID->"3e4f8336-0ac7-43c2-b6d8-c67f555ba583"],

Cell["The von Neumann entropy of any pure state |\[Psi]\:27e9 vanishes,", \
"TechNoteText",
 CellID->820980503,ExpressionUUID->"5bbb60cc-0686-474e-8a4d-b7b47fda4f2b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"S", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
       "Ket"], 
      TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
       "Bra"]}], ")"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bb1d438d-b5f7-4dcf-a662-f541ae0f2230"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2039752981,ExpressionUUID->"104d994e-f63d-4640-8829-86c3b24f7602"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "because the only non-vanishing eigenvalue of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Bra"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "30907df9-fbfa-4929-a572-7cd4163b0c5c"],
 " is 1. Physically, this is because there is no ambiguity in the quantum \
state at hand. On the other hand, the von Neumann entropy of the maximally \
mixed state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"I", "/", "d"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5534c0f9-0404-4502-9397-d3f8ec91f588"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["d", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c3360ee2-93d4-4fad-a8b4-e4d610d54593"],
 " is the dimension of the Hilbert space, is given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1731855524,ExpressionUUID->"df67907d-ccbe-442a-9b3e-1e0cde726eb1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"S", "(", 
     RowBox[{"I", "/", "d"}], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "d"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"74c08179-6ad4-4940-a5f9-fd681487946e"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1185123456,ExpressionUUID->"b9bdd496-0595-4d73-a5b1-b9054b5d9ec5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Recalling that the ",
 ButtonBox["Shannon entropy",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/ShannonEntropy"],
 " is the biggest for the uniform distribution, one can expect that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "d"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "57342abb-7ea5-4bf2-8129-a86560339f8e"],
 " is the maximum value that the von Neumann entropy can take. Indeed, we \
will later see that"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1294687020,ExpressionUUID->"fee2052d-6271-423f-85ea-5d72d4d1b92d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"0", "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"S", "(", "\[Rho]", ")"}], "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "d"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e92c51a7-0994-4c65-af61-be314c9a3c87"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1441981823,ExpressionUUID->"26fd25e7-762c-4fa1-9b12-0f7979cc106c"],

Cell["for any quantum state.", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1737238075,ExpressionUUID->"c562a800-f94e-4fbe-afb7-26d501e7ebc3"],

