  False, "RootCaptions" -> "", "HeaderCoreAreaLink" -> {}, 
  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 18, 0, 32.424050}", 
    "history" -> {"13", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "entropy", "relative entropy", "mutual entropy", "Klein's inequality", 
      "subadditivity"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "The Shannon entropy is a measure of uncertainty associated with a \
classical probability distribution. We now generalize the notion to quantum \
states described by density operators. See also Section 7.2 of the Quantum \
Workbook (2022). A classical probability distribution is associated with a \
random variable choosing values from a set of outcomes. In quantum mechanics, \
a density operator is associated with an ensemble of quantum states. One can \
imagine a quantum information source that generates messages of 'letters' \
each of which is chosen from the ensemble.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "Von Neumann Entropy", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "Von Neumann Entropy", 
    "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
